{
  "stem": "21786.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But, interestingly enough, when it came to the-- some kind of a leadership in the ghettos or the leadership in the camps, so many times these were some Zionists who were known to the SS who just picked them up at random for somebody new.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That they are capable at least to talk to them, and they knew what it is all about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And why I am saying this simply, it  is good to point for at one certain moment in time, Eva and her mother, her father, was arrested at that point, was in Czech prison, was put in a transport.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I tried somehow to get her out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Meaning, I went to the Council of the Elders where I knew one of the Zionists.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it is where this is explained to me, this is totally impossible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "For we didn't put the transport, the names together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was done by the SS themselves.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It is still one of the penalty transports for the death of the protector Heydrich, who was shot, who was killed by a Czech, by a Czech parachutist who had parachuted from Britain and succeeded to kill him.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The retribution was something absolutely enormous.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "About 40,000 people were killed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And many transports with Jew were sent towards the east.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And this was supposed to be one of the transports.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I said, but something, maybe something could be done.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He says, the only thing is that we might get in touch with people in Theresienstadt, in Terezin, where the transport will stay for about a day.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It will be shuttled then directly towards Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Maybe we'll succeed to get you out, you and Eva.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There is absolutely no guarantee.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "If you want to, try it, try it.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
